                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> (Caution - temporary thread hi-jacking ahead)<br /><br />Zrazzt - <br /><br />In order to provide a non-foolish answer to your inquiry, one has to think about what really makes drugs dangerous...is it the drugs themselves? If anyone says yes to that question, then there should be no way in hell that alcohol should be legal, should there? Alcohol is a drug - here in the states you'll see a beer commercial saying - "THIS BUDS FOR YOUUUU!!" right after a "IF YOU BUY DRUGS YOU SPONSER TERRORISM!" propaganda ad. <br /><br />Sure, any intoxicating substance, legal or not, has potential to do harm, but with alcohol the responsibility is left to the user, as it should be. We already tried prohibition, and it failed miserably, but for some reason it's a good idea to keep the black market for narcotics alive and well. <br /><br />I think what makes most drugs dangerous is their very illegality. We're providing a job market for drug dealers, smugglers, thieves, and all around low lifes. Quite often I read of drug raids gone bad, and innocent people slain. The War on Drugs is just that, a war. People die because of it. <br /><br />We should be given the responsibility to use drugs if we so feel. Let's legalize it, tax it, educate the masses, and put the real dangers out of business. I mean, fuck - here in Michigan there are teachers being laid off as a result of budget cuts -  and I don't think we are the only state. How much more money could be made from taxing the shit out of a pack of doobies and putting the drug war money towards something that might actually make a difference for someone some day? <br /><br />D.A.R.E. is a well known failure. People are always going to be using drugs. ALWAYS. That will never change, and sadly, the "land of the free" will probably be one of the last industrialized nations to get it's head out of it's ass and do something about it that will actually make a freaking difference.  [:-banghead]<br /><br /></span id="msg"></font></td>
