                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> I understand this debate will always be a hot topic. It is good that it stays that way however because it does in a sense keep abortion from becoming either too legal or too illegal. I dont believe in abortion in 98% of the cases. The 3 scenarios in which I allow leeway for people considering abortion is #1 the life of the mother is in danger. #2 The mother is the victim of a rape or incest. #3. When the baby will not survive beyond birth. Even then I think abortion should be a last resort if possible.<br /><br />   There are a few things that I really find distasteful about the Pro-choice stance. The fact that a teenager (and in some cases a very young teenager) can go into an abortion clinic and have an abortion without her parents consent or them even knowing is amazing to me. Many of the clinics dont even try to point her in another direction such as adoptive services. 15 year olds are not mature enough to make that big of a decision on thier own in my opinion. <br /><br />   Another thing I strongly disagree with is the lack of rights a father has in abortion cases. I tried to find a case from late last year to link but didnt have much time, of a father who wanted to keep the child and was denied by the courts because it was the girlfriends choice. That saddens me to think that your girlfriend or spouse can have the final say on an abortion. Just because it inconveniences her life, a willing and capable father is denied a child. <br /><br />   One of the main slogans of the pro-choice community bases thier stance on is 'A woman's right to choose' because it is her body. Well then why cant a woman choose to be a prostitute? Its her body. Prostitution is illegal because of the effect is has on the people themselves and also on the community. If you dont think that abortion that is fully legal and easily accessible won't have a negative effect on the woman and the community in the future you are mistaken. If abortion becomes non-Taboo in the future it has the potential to become a serious problem.<br /><br />    If you notice many of the people who posted in this section said they belived in abortion but were unsure about the time frame (1st or 2nd trimester). Noone really knows when a baby is "A life". I just wouldnt want to be on the wrong side of that guess.</span id="msg"></font></td>
