                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> If a 15 yrold isnt  mature enough to raise a child on thier own and doesnt have family who is willing to help then they can give it up for adoption. At least these clinics should let them know thye have options. Giving a child up for adoption is bound to have a much less traumatic effect on them later in life.<br /><br />Just because certain behaviors are accepted in certain cultures doesnt mean they arent a problem. HIV is out of control in Africa because to males there it is in a sense 'uncool' or an inconvenience to wear protection. Just because abortion isnt a big deal in some cultures doesnt mean it wont later affect the culture profoundly. <br /><br />The reason we ban a lot of things in the US are because we find them unsettling, I agree. It isnt always the whole reason either. Drugs arent banned only because we find them unsettling. They are dangerous to the individuals as well as the community. I do not believe for a second that legalizing prostitution or drugs (marajuana), or allowing abortion to become commonplace can be good for anyone. I think it would cause quite a fuss.</span id="msg"></font></td>
